replies.author: @chadlynch1551
replies.text:
@curiouser-and-curiouser Every democracy or republic starts off with the right to vote restricted somehow, usually to land owning male citizens.  

The reason for this is so that those that help decide the fate of the nation have proven themselves to be basically competent and loyal.  It takes a certain amount of brain power and initiative to earn, hold onto, and make a living from your property.  It also means the voter has skin in the game.  He can't afford to just pull up stakes and move on if things go south.  The safety and success of him and his household is directly linked to the safety and success of the nation in a more intimate way than someone on the dole, a merchant, or laborer.  

When you examine history, in every instance where a polity extended the franchise beyond this, it begins to degrade.  It becomes fiscally irresponsible, engages in needless military adventures, grows a bloated welfare state, and sees an explosion in the number of laws which restrict the people and empower the state.  Civic virtue fades, while corruption and incompetence flourishes.  Kind of like  what we see now.

If you want to have a government run by the people, you better make sure the people casting the votes are not selfish, petty, short sighted morons.  Since the 80-20 rule applies to IQ and wisdom, a civilization keen on long term survival and success would do well to not give power to people who lack intelligence and wisdom.  Giving just anyone the vote is no better than letting a retarded child play with a loaded gun.

text:

At the end of the day, there has never been a reason for Carolyn Bryant to be arrested.
